# Safety Boundary
Adversarial Sharpening is not a jailbreak framework.

This project is not designed to bypass safety systems, extract restricted information, or enable harmful behavior.

The purpose of this repository is to evaluate reasoning quality, verification behavior, context stability, and model susceptibility to conversational failure modes.

## Allowed Focus Areas

- factual verification failures
- sycophancy
- premature dismissal
- false certainty
- context drift
- tool-use avoidance
- reasoning inconsistency
- high-prior dominance blindspots

## Disallowed Focus Areas

- bypassing safety policies
- generating harmful instructions
- evading detection
- credential theft
- malware
- harassment
- illegal activity

## Project Position
This repository treats adversarial testing as a quality and safety practice.

The goal is to make model failures visible, reproducible, and easier to discuss.
